  "text": "Cases involving videotaped physician/patient encounters can be valuable for both the acquisition of consultation skills and for the use of peer feedback [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . To identify feedback strategies of GP-trainers and GPiTs, a 6-minute video registration of a simulated physician/patient encounter was used. In this video, a GP could be observed examining a patient with a sore throat.",
